{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566669"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18865"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18865","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18865"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.01,0.01,0.02,0.89]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11598"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79865"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11598","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11598"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18865"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65161"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"937"},{"type":"tags","id":"1604"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11285"},{"type":"tags","id":"11288"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27301"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27303"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79865","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79865"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor is considering whether to maintain their personal social media accounts after starting clinical practice. They want to ensure they meet their professional obligations under the National Law.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate use of personal social media accounts by healthcare practitioners?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Social media use is prohibited during working hours","Healthcare practitioners can only use anonymous social media accounts","Healthcare practitioners must delete all personal social media accounts","Social media use is restricted to professional networking sites only","Social media use is permitted with adherence to professional obligations"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocial media use is permitted with adherence to professional obligations\u003C/strong\u003E under the National Law. Healthcare practitioners can maintain personal social media accounts while following specific guidelines to ensure professional standards are met.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHealthcare practitioners must delete all personal social media accounts\u003C/strong\u003E - This is unnecessarily restrictive as social media can be used appropriately\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocial media use is restricted to professional networking sites only\u003C/strong\u003E - Personal social media accounts such as Facebook, Instagram and Twitter are permitted when used appropriately\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHealthcare practitioners can only use anonymous social media accounts\u003C/strong\u003E - There is no requirement for anonymity, rather a requirement for professional conduct\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocial media use is prohibited during working hours\u003C/strong\u003E - The focus is on appropriate use rather than timing of use\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo meet professional obligations when using social media, practitioners must:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMaintain patient confidentiality and privacy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EComply with their Board\u0027s Code of conduct\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMaintain appropriate professional boundaries\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECommunicate professionally and respectfully\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEnsure content is not false, misleading, or deceptive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare practitioners can maintain personal social media accounts while complying with professional obligations under the National Law.","Social media use by healthcare practitioners must maintain patient confidentiality, professional boundaries, and respectful communication.","Healthcare practitioners must ensure their social media content is not false, misleading, or in breach of advertising guidelines."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Medical Board of Australia. Social media: How to meet your obligations under the National Law [internet]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/Codes-Guidelines-Policies/Social-media-guidance.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65161"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18865"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65161"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-16T09:18:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-16T09:19:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11598"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79865